{
  "stem": "15694.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I saw people were there unrolling coils of barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was as if Goeth, or Goeth, discovered the weak point and made sure that it wouldn't happen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Now to speak a bit more about that camp, Plaszow, I would say that in my experience, I would answer very personal.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It w-- I felt worse there than even in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I've only esh-- talked to you about one or two incidents, but there are more.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Shortly after we arrived there, there was a manhunt going on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For one reason or another Goeth or Gate-- Goeth, Goeth wanted 150 people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we-- I don't know why we knew they were going to be killed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And to help them round up these people, usually Jewish police had to help them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I-- my father and I, we thought, well, the best place to hide is in the police barracks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we went there and because-- the wife of Sygmund Rosenblum, who was my father's cousin, and he was at a Jewish police, she made sure that we were not thrown out.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Everybody else who would try to get in would have been thrown out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And speaking of these manhunts, now at other times, there were manhunts for sm-- on small-- for small boys.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And one of these manhunts is very vividly depicted in the film, where a small boy tried frantically to hide.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And wherever he looked, somebody was already there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In the end, he ended up by hiding in the latrine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now latrine was for me when I saw it first a real shock-- a long, long board, 15, 20 yards with one hole next to each other without any partitioning, any wall, or anything.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And everybody has to do his business and nobody sort of was interested.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
